      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "INTERRO (9) resumed off the one average trial when she recorded her first win at start three, over 1100m at Goulburn with plenty up her sleeve. Drawn the inside marble again and can take the next step in this stronger contest. IN LIMBO (4) strengthened over the break and is improving with racing fourth-up. Collared late in a decent rating contest with a narrow second to Spaceballs over 1300m at Hawkesbury. A repeat effort will see her prove hard to catch. LOVE CHILD (7) is going nicely through her grades and will relish Wadick's claim from the better draw. Pushed forward from the awkward gate with a fighting head win over 1250m at Taree in C3 grade. Deep into the prep and looks up to this. MISS CAPITALE (3) total forgive from the wide gate when she came out quickly before folding up in the straight to run last over 1100m at Canterbury in BM72 class. Since fitted with a 736m tick over trial at Randwick. No surprise to see her return to form over this trip.",
